      <span class=sf-dump-str title=\"1454 characters\">&lt;p&gt;Car&lt;span style=&quot;color: var(--paragraph-color); font-family: var(--body-font1);&quot;&gt;A &lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;2&quot; data-end=&quot;9&quot; style=&quot;color: var(--paragraph-color); font-family: var(--body-font1);&quot;&gt;car&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: var(--paragraph-color); font-family: var(--body-font1);&quot;&gt; is a four-wheeled motor vehicle designed for transporting passengers. It is one of the most common modes of transportation, available in various types such as sedans, SUVs, hatchbacks, coupes, and sports cars. Cars are powered by internal combustion engines using gasoline or diesel, while modern advancements have introduced electric and hybrid vehicles for eco-friendly alternatives.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;<span class=\"sf-dump-default sf-dump-ns\">\\r\\n</span></span>
      <span class=sf-dump-str title=\"1454 characters\">&lt;p data-start=&quot;399&quot; data-end=&quot;681&quot;&gt;Cars offer convenience, speed, and comfort, making daily commuting and long-distance travel easier. Features such as air conditioning, GPS navigation, infotainment systems, and advanced safety technologies like airbags, ABS, and collision detection enhance the driving experience.&lt;/p&gt;<span class=\"sf-dump-default sf-dump-ns\">\\r\\n</span></span>
